description.narrative: UNICEF's advocacy for the care reform agenda yields government's buy in. Three county level action plans that respond to adolescent and reproductive health, HIV and SGBV were launched and the national prevention and response plan to address violence against children was finalized. National information management systems were strengthened in all 47 counties reporting age and sex-disaggregated data on HIV. Further, routine reporting of child protection data is now undertaken by 39 counties. A national child protection curriculum has been developed for frontline staff as part of social service workforce strengthening efforts. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
